OL,3,CMothers of disabled sons campaign for
OL,4,Ccameras in all care homes
OL,6,FTheir families installed cameras after
OL,7,Fbecoming concerned about the care
OL,8,Fbeing delivered. In the footage,
OL,9,FConnor was seen eating from the bin in
OL,10,Fthe middle of the night, with no carer
OL,11,Fin sight. His carers were also seen
OL,12,Ffalling asleep on shift, vaping in his
OL,13,Fliving room, and ignoring him when he
OL,14,Ftries to communicate.
OL,16,FMikey can be seen sitting in his flat,
OL,17,Fday after day, with little engagement
OL,18,Ffrom carers. He is also left alone for
OL,19,Fseveral minutes while a fire alarm
OL,20,Fgoes off in his flat.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/14
